[SN]TITLE[SN]
Llandarcy business park blaze tackled by fire crews

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Fire crews are battling a large blaze at a business park in Neath Port Talbot.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Some 50 firefighters were sent to Llancoed Court in D'Arcy Business Park, Llandarcy, near Neath, at 10:10 BST on Friday.
Mid and West Wales Fire and Rescue Service (MWWFRS) said the fire broke through the roof of a warehouse with dark smoke billowing into the air.
Three units are also at risk of collapse, the service added.
A spokesman for MWWFRS said the burning building was 80m (260ft)  by 20m (196ft) by 10m (32ft).
Crews were dispatched from Morriston, Port Talbot, Swansea Central and Swansea West.
Two crews will remain at the site overnight.
